# Vertex Workbench plugin (2026.1.x line)

- Architecture and flows: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- Features, versions, fixes: `docs/FEATURES.md`
- Agent skills: `.cursor/skills/vertex-workbench-map/`, `.cursor/skills/intellij-plugin-build/`, `.cursor/skills/dual-version-maintenance/`

When changing behavior: keep two network paths separate (localhost proxy vs direct Contents HTTPS). Do not persist GCP tokens. Match existing Kotlin/IntelliJ `@Service` patterns in `dev.vertexworkbench.pycharm`.

Build: `./scripts/build-release.sh` (runs `./gradlew test buildPlugin`) / `./gradlew runIde` (Gradle 9, Java 17). This source tree targets PyCharm Professional 2026.1.2 (`sinceBuild=261`).

## Two build lines (always port behavior changes to both)

| Line | Root | Target IDE |
|------|------|------------|
| 2025.3.x | `/Users/oleksii/Work/pycharm-plugin` | PyCharm Professional 2025.3.5/2025.3.6 (`sinceBuild=253`) |
| 2026.1.x | `/Users/oleksii/Work/pycharm-plugin/pycharm-plugin-2026.1` (this folder) | PyCharm Professional 2026.1.2 (`sinceBuild=261`) |

When fixing a bug or adding behavior that is not Jupyter-runtime-specific, apply the same patch to both lines, run `./gradlew test` and `./scripts/build-release.sh` in each, and bump the same version number in both. See `.cursor/skills/dual-version-maintenance/SKILL.md`.
